results.name: Number of partitions of n that such that no part is a Fibonacci number.
link: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..10000
formula: G.f.:  A(x) = sum(1/product(1 - x^c(i))), i >=1, where c(i) are the non-Fibonacci numbers.
mathematica: p[n_] := IntegerPartitions[n, All, Complement[Range@n, Fibonacci@Range@15]]; Table[p[n], {n, 0, 20}] (* shows partitions *)
a[n_] := Length@p@n; a /@ Range[0, 80] (* counts partitions *)
program: (PARI) N=66; q='q+O('q^N); Vec( prod(n=1,11,1-q^fibonacci(n+1))/eta(q) ) \\ _Joerg Arndt_, Mar 11 2014
results.author: _Clark Kimberling_, Mar 08 2014
